---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Card from "@components/Card.astro";
import Button from "@components/Button.astro";
const title = 'Work With Me';
const description = 'Bounded escalation formats for SAP BTP extension failures that have crossed from implementation into architectural decision failure.';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <!-- 1) Context intro -->
  <section class="stack tight">
    <h1>Independent architectural verdicts.</h1>
    <p class="measure">What you buy: a bounded architectural decision that restores jurisdiction. You send a structured page; you receive a written verdict — what must change, what must remain, and who can legitimately approve it — so delivery can proceed.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- 2) Decision‑level verdict (placed first) -->
  <section class="stack">
    <Card eyebrow="Verdict" title="Executive Boundary Verdict" class="emphasis">
      <h3>When this is the right move</h3>
      <p class="measure">Competing architectural truths cannot reconcile; no team can legitimately approve the next change. Decision impasse around trust, routing, identity, tenant, or lifecycle authority.</p>
      <h3>What you send</h3>
      <p class="measure">Landscape, divergence, timeline, ownership, and the decision that cannot converge.</p>
      <h3>What you receive</h3>
      <p class="measure">A formal written verdict defining what must change, what must remain, and who holds jurisdiction — legible for internal escalation.</p>
      <h3>What this is not</h3>
      <p class="measure">Not a rescue project; not implementation takeover; not a blame exercise.</p>
      <Button href="/contact/" variant="primary">Assess applicability</Button>
    </Card>
  </section>

  <!-- 3) Engagement spectrum (light → heavy) -->
  <h2>Engagement spectrum</h2>
  <section class="feature">
    <Card eyebrow="Rapid" title="Rapid Boundary Triage">
      <h3>When this is the right move</h3>
      <p class="measure">High‑signal incident with one or two competing narratives; Postman vs App Router/Work Zone mismatch; single‑tenant variance.</p>
      <h3>What you send</h3>
      <p class="measure">Minimal landscape plus failing path(s) with concrete divergence examples.</p>
      <h3>What you receive</h3>
      <p class="measure">Six‑boundary map, top decision points, and a brief memo with a provisional verdict.</p>
      <h3>What this is not</h3>
      <p class="measure">Not operational support; not ticket execution.</p>
      <Button href="/contact/" variant="ghost">Request triage review</Button>
    </Card>
    <Card eyebrow="Audit" title="Boundary Audit">
      <h3>When this is the right move</h3>
      <p class="measure">Fragmented ownership across teams/vendors; recurring incidents; rollout instability months after go‑live.</p>
      <h3>What you send</h3>
      <p class="measure">Landscape, divergence, stakeholder map, and representative incidents.</p>
      <h3>What you receive</h3>
      <p class="measure">Jurisdiction‑based ownership mapping, structural remediation rules, and prepared decision points for an executive verdict if required.</p>
      <h3>What this is not</h3>
      <p class="measure">Not staff augmentation; not indefinite advisory.</p>
      <Button href="/contact/" variant="ghost">Request scope discussion</Button>
    </Card>
  </section>

  <!-- 4) Why the spectrum exists (transition) -->
  <section class="stack compact">
    <p class="measure">All formats produce architectural judgment. Only the Executive Boundary Verdict defines final jurisdiction.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- 5) What I do not sell -->
  <h2>Why this is different from another round of implementation review</h2>
  <p class="measure">Implementation reviews validate local correctness; verdicts establish final jurisdiction. When behavior diverges by tenant or entry path, the defect sits in the contract — not the code. Decide the contract; then continue delivery.</p>
  <p class="measure">Prefer concrete situations? See <a href="/representative-cases/">Representative Cases</a>.</p>

  <h2>What I do not sell</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No implementation rescue or delivery services.</li>
    <li>No staff augmentation or ticket execution.</li>
    <li>No generic consulting or advisory funnel.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="measure">Need the short version? See <a href="/what-this-is-not/">What This Is Not</a>.</p>

  <!-- 6) Initiation protocol -->
  <h2>Initiation protocol</h2>
  <p class="measure">Send one structured page. That is enough to determine whether this should enter triage, audit, or verdict — fixed‑scope, time‑bounded, and outcome‑specific.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Landscape — S/4, BTP runtimes, entry surfaces, identity</li>
    <li>Divergence — by tenant, path, or surface</li>
    <li>Timeline — go‑live, rollout, recent change</li>
    <li>Ownership — who holds what today</li>
    <li>Decision — the choice that cannot converge</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:pei_jiandong@hotmail.com">pei_jiandong@hotmail.com</a> or <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/peijiandong/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
